  "answer": {
    "role": "assistant",
    "content": "<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"utf-8\" />\n  <title>Runtime Environment — Interactive Demo</title>\n  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width,initial-scale=1\" />\n  <style>\n    :root { font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, \"Segoe UI\", Roboto, \"Helvetica Neue\", Arial; color:#111; }\n    body { margin: 20px; line-height:1.45; background: #f7f9fc; }\n    h1 { margin: 0 0 8px 0; font-size: 22px; }\n    .card { background: #fff; border-radius:8px; padding:14px; box-shadow: 0 1px 3px rgba(20,30,60,0.06); margin-bottom:12px; }\n    .muted { color: #556; font-size:13px; }\n    button { border:0; background:#0b79d0; color:#fff; padding:8px 10px; border-radius:6px; cursor:pointer; }\n    button.secondary { background:#6c7a89; }\n    pre { background:#0f1720; color:#cfeef5; padding:10px; border-radius:6px; overflow:auto; font-size:13px; }\n    .row { display:flex; gap:12px; flex-wrap:wrap; }\n    .col { flex:1 1 320px; min-width:260px; }\n    .box { border:1px solid #e4eef8; border-radius:6px; padding:10px; background:#fcfeff; min-height:60px; }\n    .small { font-size:13px; color:#334; }\n    .log { font-family: monospace; font-size:13px; background:#0b1220; color:#dbeefc; padding:8px; border-radius:6px; height:140px; overflow:auto; }\n    .visual { display:flex; gap:8px; margin-top:8px; }\n    .visual .panel { flex:1; background:#fff; border:1px dashed #cfe6ff; padding:8px; border-radius:6px; min-height:80px; }\n    .task { display:inline-block; background:#0b79d0; color:white; padding:4px 8px; border-radius:4px; margin:4px 4px 0 0; font-size:13px; }\n    .micro { background:#6cbdff; }\n    .heap-item { background:#fef3c7; padding:4px 8px; border-radius:4px; margin:4px 4px 0 0; display:inline-block; font-size:13px; }\n    label { display:block; font-weight:600; margin-bottom:6px; font-size:14px; }\n    input[type=\"text\"], textarea { width:100%; padding:8px; border-radius:6px; border:1px solid #dbeaf8; font-family:monospace; }\n    details { margin-top:8px; }\n    footer { margin-top:18px; font-size:12px; color:#556; }\n    a { color:#0b79d0; text-decoration:none; }\n  </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n  <div class=\"card\">\n    <h1>Runtime Environment — Interactive Demo</h1>\n    <div class=\"muted\">A runtime environment is the system that executes code and provides services (APIs, scheduling, memory management, globals). This page demonstrates core ideas using browser JavaScript.</div>\n  </div>\n\n  <div class=\"card\">\n    <label>Detect: what runtime are we in?</label>\n    <div class=\"row\">\n      <div class=\"col box\">\n        <div class=\"small\">Click to inspect global environment values available to this JavaScript runtime.</div>\n        <div style=\"margin-top:8px;\">\n          <button id=\"btn-detect\">Detect Runtime</button>\n          <button id=\"btn-clear\" class=\"secondary\">Clear</button>\n        </div>\n        <pre id=\"detectOut\" style=\"margin-top:8px;\">(results appear here)</pre>\n      </div>\n\n      <div class=\"col box\">\n        <div class=\"small\">Interpretation for these results:</div>\n        <div id=\"detectExplain\" style=\"margin-top:8px;\">\n          We're running inside a browser-like JS runtime (window exists). In Node.js you'd see a \"process\" global and different available APIs (fs, path, process.env).\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n\n  <div class=\"card\">\n    <label>Event Loop, Call Stack, Microtasks vs Macrotasks (interactive)</label>\n    <div class=\"small\">Click \"Run demo\" to visualize how synchronous code, microtasks (Promises), and macrotasks (setTimeout) are ordered by the runtime.</div>\n    <div style=\"margin-top:8px;\">\n      <button id=\"btn-run\">Run demo</button>\n      <button id=\"btn-step\" class=\"secondary\">Step through</button>\n      <button id=\"btn-reset\" class=\"secondary\">Reset</button>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"visual\" style=\"margin-top:12px;\">\n      <div class=\"panel\">\n        <div style=\"font-weight:700\">Call Stack</div>\n        <div id=\"stack\" style=\"min-height:70px; margin-top:8px;\"></div>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"panel\">\n        <div style=\"font-weight:700\">Microtask Queue (Promise.then)</div>\n        <div id=\"micro\" style=\"min-height:70px; margin-top:8px;\"></div>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"panel\">\n        <div style=\"font-weight:700\">Macrotask Queue (setTimeout)</div>\n        <div id=\"macro\" style=\"min-height:70px; margin-top:8px;\"></div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <div style=\"margin-top:10px;\">\n      <div style=\"font-weight:700\">Console (order of logs)</div>\n      <div id=\"elog\" class=\"log\"></div>\n    </div>\n\n    <details style=\"margin-top:10px\">\n      <summary style=\"cursor:pointer\">See the code used in this demo</summary>\n      <pre>\nfunction demo() {\n  log('script start');\n  queueMacro('setTimeout callback', () => log('from macrotask'));\n  queueMicro('Promise.then callback', () => log('from microtask'));\n  log('script end');\n}\n      </pre>\n    </details>\n  </div>\n\n  <div class=\"card\">\n    <label>Web Worker (separate runtime thread)</label>\n    <div class=\"small\">Spawns a worker: it has its own global scope (no DOM), can postMessage with the main runtime.</div>\n    <div style=\"margin-top:8px;\">\n      <button id=\"btn-worker\">Start Worker</button>\n      <button id=\"btn-worker-stop\" class=\"secondary\">Stop Worker</button>\n      <div id=\"workerOut\" style=\"margin-top:8px;\" class=\"box small\">Worker not started.</div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n\n  <div class=\"card\">\n    <label>Sandboxed iframe runner (isolated environment)</label>\n    <div class=\"small\">Run user code inside a sandboxed iframe (allow-scripts only) so it can't access this page's DOM or cookies. It communicates only via postMessage.</div>\n    <textarea id=\"runnerCode\" rows=\"6\">// Try simple code:\npostMessage({type:'log', text: 'Hello from sandbox'});\n// You can use console.log, but we forward messages back to the parent:\nconsole.log('console inside iframe');\n</textarea>\n    <div style=\"margin-top:8px;\">\n      <button id=\"btn-run-sandbox\">Run in Sandbox</button>\n      <button id=\"btn-remove-sandbox\" class=\"secondary\">Remove Sandbox</button>\n    </div>\n    <div id=\"sandboxOut\" style=\"margin-top:8px;\" class=\"box small\">Sandbox output appears here.</div>\n  </div>\n\n  <div class=\"card\">\n    <label>APIs provided by the runtime (examples)</label>\n    <div class=\"small\">The runtime provides built-in APIs. Some exist in browsers, others only in Node.js.</div>\n    <ul>\n      <li><strong>Browser runtime:</strong> DOM (document), fetch, localStorage, Web Workers, WebSockets, Web Crypto.</li>\n      <li><strong>Node.js runtime:</strong> filesystem (fs), process, Buffer, native modules, global require.</li>\n      <li><strong>Common:</strong> memory (heap), call stack, scheduler/event loop, garbage collector, globalThis.</li>\n    </ul>\n    <details>\n      <summary style=\"cursor:pointer\">Show short code examples for Node-only APIs (do not run here)</summary>\n      <pre>// Node-only (do not run in browser):\nconst fs = require('fs');\nconst content = fs.readFileSync('/path/file.txt', 'utf8');\nconsole.log(process.env.PATH);\n</pre>\n    </details>\n  </div>\n\n  <footer>\n    Tip: This demonstration runs in the browser's JavaScript runtime. To explore Node.js runtime, run similar examples inside Node (node REPL or a script).\n  </footer>\n\n<script>\n/* Utility logging */\nfunction appendLog(el, text) {\n  el.textContent += text + \"\\\\n\";\n  el.scrollTop = el.scrollHeight;\n}\n\n/* Detect runtime */\nconst detectOut = document.getElementById('detectOut');\ndocument.getElementById('btn-detect').addEventListener('click', () => {\n  detectOut.textContent = '';\n  const lines = [];\n  try {\n    lines.push('globalThis type: ' + typeof globalThis);\n    lines.push('window exists: ' + (typeof window !== 'undefined'));\n    lines.push('document exists: ' + (typeof document !== 'undefined'));\n    lines.push('process exists: ' + (typeof process !== 'undefined'));\n    lines.push('navigator.userAgent: ' + (typeof navigator !== 'undefined' ? navigator.userAgent : 'n/a'));\n    lines.push('worker? (typeof Worker): ' + (typeof Worker !== 'undefined'));\n    detectOut.textContent = lines.join('\\\\n');\n  } catch (e) {\n    detectOut.textContent = String(e);\n  }\n});\ndocument.getElementById('btn-clear').addEventListener('click', () => detectOut.textContent = '(results appear here)');\n\n/* Event loop visualizer */\nconst stackEl = document.getElementById('stack');\nconst microEl = document.getElementById('micro');\nconst macroEl = document.getElementById('macro');\nconst elog = document.getElementById('elog');\n\nfunction clearVis() {\n  stackEl.innerHTML = '';\n  microEl.innerHTML = '';\n  macroEl.innerHTML = '';\n  elog.textContent = '';\n  state = {stepMode:false, steps:[], running:false};\n}\nlet state = {stepMode:false, steps:[], running:false};\nclearVis();\n\nfunction pushStack(name) {\n  const d = document.createElement('div');\n  d.className = 'task';\n  d.textContent = name;\n  stackEl.appendChild(d);\n  return d;\n}\nfunction popStack() {\n  if (stackEl.lastChild) stackEl.removeChild(stackEl.lastChild);\n}\n\nfunction addMicro(name) {\n  const d = document.createElement('div'); d.className='task micro'; d.textContent=name; microEl.appendChild(d); return d;\n}\nfunction addMacro(name) {\n  const d = document.createElement('div'); d.className='task'; d.textContent=name; macroEl.appendChild(d); return d;\n}\n\nfunction visualizeRun() {\n  clearVis();\n  elog.textContent = '';\n  // We'll perform synchronous logs, schedule micro and macro tasks.\n  state.running = true;\n  // Define actions to animate in steps (not to be confused with real microtasks/ macrotasks)\n  // Step 1: script start -> on call stack\n  const step = (label, fn) => state.steps.push({label, fn});\n  step('push main', () => {\n    pushStack('main()');\n    appendLog(elog, 'script start (sync)');\n  });\n  step('schedule macrotask', () => {\n    addMacro('setTimeout callback');\n    setTimeout(() => {\n      // real macrotask will run after microtasks; we animate when macrotask actually executes\n      // push to stack to show macrotask execution\n    }, 0);\n    appendLog(elog, 'scheduled macrotask (setTimeout)');\n  });\n  step('schedule microtask', () => {\n    addMicro('Promise.then callback');\n    Promise.resolve().then(() => {\n      // microtask will run after current call stack unwinds; we animate here using microtask queue\n    });\n    appendLog(elog, 'scheduled microtask (Promise.then)');\n  });\n  step('sync end', () => {\n    appendLog(elog, 'script end (sync)');\n  });\n  step('pop main', () => {\n    popStack();\n  });\n  // Microtask consumption (executed before macrotasks)\n  step('run microtasks', () => {\n    // take visuals from microEl and animate their execution\n    if (microEl.lastChild) {\n      const txt = microEl.lastChild.textContent;\n      appendLog(elog, 'running microtask -> ' + txt);\n      const el = microEl.lastChild;\n      addToStackFromNode(el);\n      setTimeout(() => {\n        // simulate execution\n        popStack();\n        microEl.removeChild(el);\n      }, 200);\n    } else {\n      appendLog(elog, 'no microtasks to run');\n    }\n  });\n  // Macrotask consumption\n  step('run macrotasks', () => {\n    if (macroEl.lastChild) {\n      const txt = macroEl.lastChild.textContent;\n      appendLog(elog, 'running macrotask -> ' + txt);\n      const el = macroEl.lastChild;\n      addToStackFromNode(el);\n      setTimeout(() => {\n        popStack();\n        macroEl.removeChild(el);\n      }, 200);\n    } else {\n      appendLog(elog, 'no macrotasks to run');\n    }\n  });\n  step('done', () => { appendLog(elog, '-- demo complete --'); state.running = false; });\n\n  // If step mode: don't auto-run steps; allow manual stepping.\n  if (!state.stepMode) {\n    (async function play() {\n      for (let i=0;i<state.steps.length;i++){\n        state.steps[i].fn();\n        await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 350));\n      }\n    })();\n  } else {\n    appendLog(elog, 'Step mode ON: click Step through to advance.');\n  }\n}\nfunction addToStackFromNode(node) {\n  const name = node.textContent;\n  pushStack(name);\n}\n\n/* Buttons */\ndocument.getElementById('btn-run').addEventListener('click', () => {\n  state.stepMode = false;\n  visualizeRun();\n});\ndocument.getElementById('btn-step').addEventListener('click', () => {\n  if (!state.running || state.steps.length === 0) {\n    // Initialize in step mode\n    state.stepMode = true;\n    visualizeRun();\n  }\n  if (state.steps.length > 0) {\n    const step = state.steps.shift();\n    step.fn();\n  } else {\n    appendLog(elog, '(no more steps)');\n  }\n});\ndocument.getElementById('btn-reset').addEventListener('click', clearVis);\n\n/* Web Worker demo */\nlet myWorker = null;\nconst workerOut = document.getElementById('workerOut');\ndocument.getElementById('btn-worker').addEventListener('click', () => {\n  if (myWorker) { workerOut.textContent = 'Worker already running.'; return; }\n  const workerCode = `\n    self.onmessage = function(e) {\n      if (e.data === 'ping') {\n        self.postMessage({type:'pong', text: 'pong from worker'});\n      } else if (e.data === 'who') {\n        // Worker global: no DOM, no window, but 'self' exists\n        self.postMessage({type:'info', text: 'worker_global_keys:' + Object.keys(self).slice(0,8).join(',')});\n      }\n    };\n    // send ready message\n    self.postMessage({type:'ready', text:'worker ready'});\n  `;\n  const blob = new Blob([workerCode], { type: 'text/javascript' });\n  const url = URL.createObjectURL(blob);\n  myWorker = new Worker(url);\n  myWorker.onmessage = function(ev) {\n    const d = ev.data;\n    if (d.type === 'ready') workerOut.textContent = 'Worker ready.';\n    else if (d.type === 'pong') workerOut.textContent = d.text;\n    else if (d.type === 'info') workerOut.textContent = d.text;\n    else workerOut.textContent = 'msg: ' + JSON.stringify(d);\n  };\n  // test ping\n  myWorker.postMessage('ping');\n  // ask who it is\n  myWorker.postMessage('who');\n});\ndocument.getElementById('btn-worker-stop').addEventListener('click', () => {\n  if (!myWorker) { workerOut.textContent = 'Worker not running.'; return; }\n  myWorker.terminate();\n  myWorker = null;\n  workerOut.textContent = 'Worker stopped.';\n});\n\n/* Sandboxed iframe runner */\nlet sandboxIframe = null;\nconst sandboxOut = document.getElementById('sandboxOut');\ndocument.getElementById('btn-run-sandbox').addEventListener('click', () => {\n  if (sandboxIframe) {\n    sandboxOut.textContent = 'Sandbox already exists. Posting code...';\n    postCodeToSandbox();\n    return;\n  }\n  // Create sandboxed iframe with allow-scripts but no same-origin\n  sandboxIframe = document.createElement('iframe');\n  sandboxIframe.setAttribute('sandbox', 'allow-scripts'); // no same-origin => isolation\n  sandboxIframe.style.display = 'none';\n  // The iframe content listens for messages and executes code\n  const runnerHTML = `\n    <!doctype html><meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n    <script>\n      // NOTE: This iframe is sandboxed and cannot access parent DOM or cookies.\n      window.addEventListener('message', function(e){\n        try {\n          const code = e.data && e.data.code;\n          // Provide a simple API: postMessage({type:'log', text: ...})\n          function post(obj) { parent.postMessage(obj, '*'); }\n          // Capture console.log\n          const origLog = console.log;\n          console.log = function(...args) { post({type:'console', text: args.map(String).join(' ')}); origLog.apply(console, args); };\n          // Run the code\n          const result = (function(){\n            return eval('(async function(){' + code + '\\\\n})()');\n          })();\n          Promise.resolve(result).then(r => post({type:'result', text: String(r)})).catch(err => post({type:'error', text: String(err)}));\n        } catch (err) {\n          parent.postMessage({type:'error', text: String(err)}, '*');\n        }\n      }, false);\n      // notify parent ready\n      parent.postMessage({type:'ready', text:'iframe ready'}, '*');\n    <\\/script>\n  `;\n  sandboxIframe.srcdoc = runnerHTML;\n  document.body.appendChild(sandboxIframe);\n\n  window.addEventListener('message', handleSandboxMessage);\n  function handleSandboxMessage(ev) {\n    if (!sandboxIframe) return;\n    const d = ev.data;\n    if (d && d.type) {\n      if (d.type === 'ready') sandboxOut.textContent = 'Sandbox ready. Posting code...';\n      else if (d.type === 'console') sandboxOut.textContent += '[console] ' + d.text + '\\\\n';\n      else if (d.type === 'result') sandboxOut.textContent += '[result] ' + d.text + '\\\\n';\n      else if (d.type === 'error') sandboxOut.textContent += '[error] ' + d.text + '\\\\n';\n    }\n  }\n  // slight delay to allow iframe load\n  setTimeout(postCodeToSandbox, 120);\n});\n\nfunction postCodeToSandbox() {\n  if (!sandboxIframe) { sandboxOut.textContent = 'No sandbox iframe.'; return; }\n  sandboxOut.textContent = '';\n  const code = document.getElementById('runnerCode').value;\n  sandboxIframe.contentWindow.postMessage({code}, '*');\n}\n\ndocument.getElementById('btn-remove-sandbox').addEventListener('click', () => {\n  if (!sandboxIframe) { sandboxOut.textContent = 'No sandbox to remove.'; return; }\n  sandboxIframe.remove();\n  sandboxIframe = null;\n  sandboxOut.textContent = 'Sandbox removed.';\n});\n\n/* Prevent potential runaway scripts in sandbox (we rely on iframe isolation) */\n\n/* Notes:\n - This page demonstrates features of a runtime:\n   * detection of global objects,\n   * the event loop ordering (sync -> microtasks -> macrotasks),\n   * separate runtimes like Web Workers,\n   * sandbox isolation via iframe.\n - Node.js has different built-in APIs; to explore Node-specific behavior, run similar code in Node.\n*/\n\n/* Quick explanation auto-run: show detection by default */\ndocument.getElementById('btn-detect').click();\n</script>\n</body>\n</html>"
  },
